# Block Themes

## Theme.json
- Define global styles and settings in `theme.json`
- Configure color palettes, typography, layout settings
- Set block-specific styles and settings
- Use semantic design tokens for consistency

## Template Structure
- Place block templates in `templates/` directory (HTML files)
- Place template parts in `parts/` directory (header.html, footer.html)
- Use block markup syntax with HTML comments

## Custom Post Types
- Set `show_in_rest => true` to enable Gutenberg editor
- Define block templates with `template` and `template_lock` parameters

## Patterns
- Create block patterns in `patterns/` directory
- Register with proper pattern header

## Compatibility
- Test with both classic and block editor
- Provide backwards compatibility for classic templates if needed
- Ensure theme works with Full Site Editing (FSE)
